# Cypress Conventions

- Use `data-cy` attributes for selectors — keep tests decoupled from styling and structure
- Never use `cy.wait(ms)` for arbitrary delays — use `cy.intercept` + `cy.wait("@alias")` for network
- Chain assertions directly — avoid storing Cypress subjects in variables
- Use `beforeEach` for common navigation/setup, not `before`
- Use `cy.intercept` to stub API responses for deterministic tests

```typescript
// ❌ BAD
cy.get(".btn-submit").click();
cy.wait(5000);
cy.get(".toast").should("exist");

// ✅ GOOD
cy.intercept("POST", "/api/users").as("createUser");
cy.get("[data-cy=submit-button]").click();
cy.wait("@createUser").its("response.statusCode").should("eq", 201);
cy.get("[data-cy=success-toast]").should("be.visible");
```
